<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Astros Place Caminiti on DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Houston third baseman Ken Caminiti was  
placed on the 15-day disabled list Saturday because of a strained 
right calf muscle. 
</P>
<P>
	Caminiti hurt himself stealing a base in Friday night's 4-3 loss  
to the San Francisco Giants. 
</P>
<P>
	The Astros recalled infielder Daryle Ward to fill Caminiti's  
roster spot. Ward, who was batting .339 in 42 games at Triple-A New 
Orleans, will join the Astros in San Francisco in time for Sunday's 
series final. 
</P>
<P>
	Caminiti, batting .292 with two home runs and 17 RBIs, was hurt  
while stealing second. He appeared to cramp up shortly after 
driving off first base and grabbed his leg in pain as he neared 
second, managing to slide around shortstop Rich Aurilia's tag to 
complete the steal. 
</P>
<P>
	Caminiti limped off the field and into the club house for  
treatment. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's pretty sore. I'm having a hard time walking,'' Caminiti  
said after the game. ``I'm having a hard time with this because I 
wanted to come back and have a healthy year. Now this same old 
stuff, it's just kind of making me mad right now.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
