<HEADLINE> Golden Temper Wins at Churchill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Golden Temper cruised to a 4 1/2-length  
victory over Boom Town Girl in the $111,400 Dogwood Stakes Saturday 
at Churchill Downs. 
</P>
<P>
	Golden Temper, with Shane Sellers aboard, covered the 1 1/16  
miles in 1:43 2/5 and paid $6, $3.80 and $3.40. Boom Town Girl 
closed from seventh on the backside and paid $11.40 and $7.80. 
Honey Hill Lil, at 19-1, opened up a three-length lead around the 
far turn but tired down the lane and paid $6.20. 
</P>
<P>
	Owned by Mark Stanley, Golden Temper earned $69,068 to boost her  
lifetime earnings to $188,346. The win was the fourth in eight 
career starts and third in five tries this year. 
</P>
