<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> DuPont's Acquisition of Pioneer OK'd </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The U.S. Department of Justice is allowing  
DuPont Co. to proceed with its acquisition of Pioneer Hi-Bred 
International Inc., the world's largest seed corn company. 
</P>
<P>
	With the Justice raising no objections, the only remaining  
obstacles are the approval of Pioneer shareholders and the European 
Union, said Susan Gaffney, a DuPont spokeswoman on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Gaffney said the merger is expected to be completed this summer.  
</P>
<P>
	DuPont, which already owns 20 percent of Pioneer, will pay an  
estimated $7.7 billion for the remaining 80 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Pioneer shareholders will receive $40 per share, with 45 percent  
of the shares being traded for cash and the remainder for DuPont 
stock. 
</P>
<P>
	Headquartered in Des Moines, Iowa, Pioneer Hi-Bred is an  
agricultural genetics and technology company that produces seeds 
and grain additives. 
</P>
<P>
	DuPont, based in Wilmington, Del., hopes the merger will  
strengthen and accelerate the company's ability to develop new 
agricultural and food products. 

</P>
</TEXT>
