<HEADLINE> Rapids 2, MetroStars 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- Paul Bravo scored twice as the Colorado Rapids  
extended their team-record winning streak to six games with a 2-0 
victory over the New York-New Jersey MetroStars on Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Colorado (6-2) goalkeeper Marcus Hahnemann made three saves for  
his second straight shutout. Hahnemann has not allowed a goal in 
182 minutes. 
</P>
