<HEADLINE> Students Hurt in Georgia Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Students injured in Thursday's shooting at Heritage High School  
in Conyers, Ga.: 
</P>
<P>
	--Stephanie Laster, 15, hit in buttocks by a bullet, which passed  
through to her intestines. Listed in fair condition Friday and 
expected to remain several days at Hughes Spalding Children's 
Hospital in Atlanta. 
</P>
<P>
	--Brian Barnhardt, 16, shot in buttocks. Released Friday in good  
condition from Rockdale Hospital in Conyers. 
</P>
<P>
	--Jason Cheek, 17, shot twice in leg. Released Friday in good  
condition from Rockdale Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	--Cania Cullins, 15, hit in the knee; bullet still lodged there.  
Listed in good condition Friday and expected to remain another day 
or so at Rockdale Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	--Drake Hoy, 17, shot in foot. Treated and released from Rockdale  
Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	--Ryan Rosa, 18, shot in the right ankle. Treated and released  
from Rockdale Hospital. 
</P>
