<DOCNO> APW19990522.0095 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-22 17:51:23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Angels' Pitcher Hits Three Straight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- Anaheim knuckleballer Steve Sparks  
tied a major league record by hitting three straight batters in the 
third inning Saturday night against the Tampa Bay Devil Rays, two 
of them with the bases-loaded. 
</P>
<P>
	Sparks also hit Jose Canseco in the first inning, giving him  
four overall to tie the major league mark for a nine-inning game 
since 1900. 
</P>
<P>
	The right-hander hit Paul Sorrento to load the bases with two  
outs in the third. He then hit the next two batters, Miguel Cairo 
and Kevin Stocker, to force in two runs that gave Tampa Bay a 3-2 
lead. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the fourth time in modern history a pitcher has hit three  
consecutive batters. The others were Houston's C.J. Nitkowski 
(1988), the Chicago White Sox's Wilbur Wood (1977) and Pittsburgh's 
Dock Ellis (1974). 
</P>
<P>
	Sparks became the first AL pitcher since Bert Blyleven on April  
22, 1988, to hit four batters in a game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
