<HEADLINE> Fire 3, Wizards 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Diego Gutierrez scored two goals against his  
former team as the Chicago Fire defeated the Kansas City Wizards 
3-1 on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Fire (6-3) kept its hold on first place in the Western  
Conference of the MLS, snapping a two-game losing streak. Kansas 
City remains in the cellar at 1-8. 
</P>
<P>
	Gutierrez scored in the 27th and 76th minutes. The midfielder  
appeared in 28 games for Kansas City in 1996 before suffering a 
devastating knee injury in 1997. Chicago picked up Gutierrez in the 
eighth round of the MLS expansion draft, and he became a key 
component of the Fire's 1998 title run. 
</P>
<P>
	Gutierrez scored his first goal on the rebound of a Ante Razov  
shot that struck the left post and dribbled to the top of the 
Wizards penalty area and ripped a 22-yard shot into the left corner 
of the net for his second. 
</P>
<P>
	Josh Wolff scored the Fire's first goal of the night, slashing  
through the penalty area to reach a pass from Jerzy Podbrozny and 
slip a shot past Wizards goalkeeper Chris Snitko in the 17th 
minute. 
</P>
<P>
	Mo Johnston scored the lone goal for Kansas City, netting a  
header on a cross from Jake Dancy in the 57th minute. Preki also 
assisted on the play. 
</P>
