<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990522.0112 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-22 14:31:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> D.C. United 3, Fusion 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) -- Major League Soccer scoring leader  
Roy Lassiter had two second-half goals and Marco Etcheverry added a 
spectacular finale, giving D.C. United a 3-1 win over the Miami 
Fusion Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Lassiter has 10 goals in only eight games this season.  
</P>
<P>
	Etcheverry scored in the 90th minute on a shot over goalkeeper  
Jeff Cassar from just inside the midfield line. Cassar had moved 
forward as the Fusion pressed for a late tying goal. 
</P>
<P>
	D.C. improved to 6-3 with its third straight victory. Miami lost  
its fourth straight, falling to 3-7. 
</P>
<P>
	The Fusion missed a chance to score the game's first goal with  
30 seconds remaining in the first half, when Mickey Trotman shot 
into the side netting with goalkeeper Tom Presthus out of position. 
</P>
<P>
	The teams managed only one shot on goal in the half.  
</P>
<P>
	United entered the game as MLS's highest scoring team with 18  
goals, but didn't put a shot on goal until Lassiter scored in the 
62nd minute. Lassiter won a short cross from D.C. midfielder Richie 
Williams in front of Cassar and easily beat the goalie inside the 
6-yard box. 
</P>
<P>
	Lassiter made it 2-0 eight minutes later, after intercepting a  
Fusion backpass intended for Cassar from defender Pablo Mastroeni. 
</P>
<P>
	Miami pulled within 2-1 on a Diego Serna goal in the 80th  
minute. Serna's fifth goal came on a header as he deflected a kick 
by John Maessner over the D.C. defense. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
