<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Manchester United Wins F.A. Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WEMBLEY, England (AP) -- Manchester United kept alive its bid for  
an unprecedented triple sweep in soccer by beating Newcastle 2-0 
Saturday to win the F.A. Cup. 
</P>
<P>
	Teddy Sheringham and Paul Scholes scored the goals.  
</P>
<P>
	United, unbeaten in 32 games, earlier won the Premier League  
title. It can become the first to win all three major European 
trophies in one season by beating Bayern Munich in Barcelona on 
Wednesday in the European Champions Cup. 
</P>
<P>
	Sheringham scored in the 10th minute from 16 yards, just 90  
seconds after he went into the game as a substitute for injured Roy 
Keane. Scholes added the final goal from 18 yards out in the 53rd 
minute on a defensive error by Nicos Dabizas. 
</P>
<P>
	The game was the season finale for English soccer and drew a  
capacity crowd of 80,000 to Wembley in north London. 
</P>
<P>
	The F.A. Cup was the Reds' record 10th and gave coach Alex  
Ferguson's team its third league and cup double of the decade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
