<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Showers dampened parts of the South on Saturday, while storms  
also rumbled through the Plains and Rockies. 
</P>
<P>
	Showers and thunderstorms stretched across much of the eastern  
Ohio Valley and down into the northern Gulf States by way of the 
Appalachians. Most were light to moderate. 
</P>
<P>
	Across much of Florida, the afternoon seabreeze front spawned a  
few showers and thunderstorms. 
</P>
<P>
	A system skirting the northern Plains brought showers and  
thunderstorms to much of the region, including flood-weary North 
Dakota. 
</P>
<P>
	To the south, a band of storms developed across southern  
Nebraska and through Kansas, just touching the Oklahoma border. 
</P>
<P>
	A cold front moving through the central Rockies produced widely  
scattered showers over Wyoming, Colorado, Utah and Nevada. 
</P>
<P>
	The Pacific Coast was fair to partly cloudy .  
</P>
<P>
	emperatures across the Lower 48 ranged from a low of 27 in  
Stanley, Idaho, to an early-afternoon high of 88 in McAllen, Texas. 
With the wind chill, it felt like zero in Sheridan, Wyo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
