<HEADLINE> Gellar Learns Love Scene Moves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Sarah Michelle Gellar learned a few moves  
smooching on the playground she can use now in on-screen love 
scenes. 
</P>
<P>
	``Making out in parks is a very big thing to do in high school  
when you grow up in New York City,'' Gellar, 22, says in the June 
issue of Cosmopolitan. ``There was a playground right near my home 
and the swings saw a lot of action from me.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The star of ``Buffy the Vampire Slayer'' on TV and films  
including ``Scream 2,'' ``I Know What You Did Last Summer'' and 
``Simply Irresistible,'' won a daytime Emmy before ``Buffy'' for 
work on the soap opera ``All My Children.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Her on-camera kissing skills got the ultimate test in ``Cruel  
Intentions,'' when the script called for a girl-on-girl lip lock 
with Selma Blair, currently starring in ``Zoe, Duncan, Jack &AMP; 
Jane.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``I kept thinking, I have had to kiss guys that I don't want to  
kiss,'' she said. ``At least Selma is a friend and I know where 
she's been.'' 
</P>
